161 A.3d 718 In the MATTER OF the PETITION FOR REINSTATEMENT OF Robert L. KLINE, III to the Bar of Maryland Misc. Docket AG No. 111,

Sept. Term, 2016

Court of Appeals of Maryland. June 5, 2017

ORDER

The Court having considered the Petition for Reinstatement to the Maryland Bar filed by Petitioner, Robert L. Kline, III, and the response of Bar Counsel filed in the above entitled case, it is this 5th day of June, 2017

ORDERED, by the Court of Appeals of Maryland, a majority of the Court concurring, that the Petition for Reinstatement of Robert L. Kline, III be, and it is hereby, granted, and it is further

ORDERED, that Petitioner, upon taking in open court and subscribing to the oath of attorneys required by MD Code (2004), Business Occupations and Professions Article Sec. 10-212, be reinstated as a member of the Bar of Maryland, and it is further

ORDERED that the Clerk of the Court shall replace the name of Robert L. Kline, III upon the register of attorneys entitled to practice in this Court and certify that fact to the Trustees of the Client Protection Fund and the Clerks of all judicial tribunals in this State.
